# Loup marketing site (V2)

Premium screen-free kid phone ($149) for anxious parents. Stack: Next.js App Router, `loupkids-theme`, `LoupkidsShell`.

## Visual reference

Match **https://loupkids.com** hierarchy: Inter, black/white editorial, minimal. Improve **conversion copy and proof**, not campaign chrome.

- **Public site:** `LoupkidsShell` + `src/components/loupkids/`
- **Campaign only:** `/launch` (noindex) — bold color blocks; do not spread to `/`, `/shop`, `/journal`, etc.
- **Do not** add Fable card grids, “Start here” badges, or onboarding widgets to journal/shop pages.

## One funnel

`/` → `/shop/loup` → cart → checkout

- **One CTA verb:** `Reserve Loup — $149` (short: `Order Loup`)
- Reuse `src/lib/content/loupkids-conversion.ts` and `src/components/loupkids/conversion/` — extend, don’t reinvent
- **Proof before price:** `LoupkidsStarRating` under hero H1; `LoupkidsGuaranteeBadge` under every buy/checkout button
- **Depth on PDP only:** comparison, specs, full reviews — not duplicated on homepage

## Homepage limits (~7 sections)

Hero → press/stats → features (`LoupkidsFeatureGrid`) → story (2 sentences + link to `/about`) → testimonials → CTA → footer.

- **One feature section** — loupkids.com accordion on the black phone band (`LoupkidsAccordion` + `LOUPKIDS_ACCORDION`). No emoji cards, no `LoupkidsFeatureGrid` on homepage.
- Companion section = app GIF + link to `/setup` only

## Information architecture

| Route | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `/resources` | Parent guides + curated journal links |
| `/help` | Product setup, app, billing, troubleshooting |
| `/journal` | Title + article list only (simple, like loupkids.com) |
| `/about` | Canonical founder story (`/story` redirects here) |

Cross-link Resources ↔ Help in page headers; don’t duplicate Start Here blocks.

## Non-negotiables

1. No fake forms — mailto or remove until backend exists
2. No new pages, nav items, or markdown docs unless the user asks
3. No feature-first hero headlines — benefit/emotion + safety/peace of mind
4. Minimize scope; delete duplicates instead of adding “polish”
5. `npm run build` must pass after substantive changes

## Agent workflow

**Before editing:** List what you’ll change and what duplicate content you’ll remove.

**When user says “Fable content”:** written copy (guides, KB, media kit) — **not** Fable campaign UI patterns.

**After editing:** Summarize hero + PDP impact only; don’t dump full diffs unless asked.
